summary:
I have fixed the hash collision bug in `src/Product.java`. 

The `hashCode()` method was originally using the `category` string to generate its hash. Since there were only 10 unique categories for 10,000 items, this caused massive collisions and forced the `ProductCache` into a state of O(n) lookups across long chain entries.

I updated `hashCode()` to use the unique `sku` instead:

```java
    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return sku.hashCode();
    }
```

This properly distributes the entries across the buckets. I have rebuilt the classes and run `test.sh`, which now successfully passes with the max chain length drastically reduced from ~1000 down to 4.
